details.name: Cheltenham Town F.C.
details.text: Cheltenham Town Football Club is a professional association football club based in the town of Cheltenham, Gloucestershire, England.

details.name: Northampton Town F.C.
details.text: Northampton Town Football Club is a professional association football club based in the town of Northampton, England.

details.name: Doncaster Rovers F.C.
details.text: Doncaster Rovers Football Club is a professional association football club based in the town of Doncaster, South Yorkshire, England.

details.name: UEFA Women's Championship
details.text: The UEFA European Women's Championship, also called the UEFA Women's Euro, held every four years, is the main competition in women's association football between national teams of the UEFA confederation.

details.name: Villa Park
details.text: Villa Park is a football stadium in Aston, Birmingham, England, with a seating capacity of 42,749.

details.name: UEFA European Under-21 Championship
details.text: The UEFA European Under-21 Championship, the UEFA Under-21 Championship or simply the Euro Under-21, is a biennial football competition contested by the European men's under-21 national teams of the UEFA member associations.

details.name: AFC Bournemouth
details.text: AFC Bournemouth ( (listen)) is a professional association football club based in Kings Park, Boscombe, a suburb of Bournemouth, Dorset, England.
